  CORE ARGUMENT: Grant and Booth provide a systematic typology of 14 distinct review types (including systematic reviews, scoping reviews, meta-analyses, critical reviews, and literature reviews) and analyze their associated methodologies using the SALSA framework (Search, AppraisaL, Synthesis, and Analysis). They clarify the defining characteristics, purposes, and methodological requirements of each review type, addressing widespread confusion about review terminology and methodology.

